      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "High-density zoning is a powerful tool for urban sustainability because it drastically reduces per-capita energy consumption by supporting efficient public transit and walkable neighborhoods. This concentration of people also fosters stronger social equity by increasing housing supply, which can help stabilize rental costs in otherwise prohibitively expensive metro areas. Furthermore, dense urban cores allow for more efficient use of limited land resources, preserving surrounding green spaces. Ultimately, this model creates vibrant, economically diverse, and environmentally responsible communities.",
